Sign up here to get Inside the Nets delivered to your inbox each Saturday morning. Ever since the trade deadline, Bruce Brown has been playing like a new man. Or maybe like his old self. Yes, the James Harden trade opened up playing time for Brown – DeAndre’ Bembry was waived in the Nets’ roster shuffle and centerpiece acquisition Ben Simmons has not been ready to enter the lineup. Brown has started every game since the Harden deal was made official on Feb. 12. But the Nets’ defensive spark plug says his revival is about more than minutes.